column9:
*تحديث #حملة_سند وفق آخر المستجدات على الأرض*

بعد الحملة الأولى التي كللت بالنجاح، تم توفير مساعدات مهمة ونوعية ل 15 دوارا معزولا بجماعة اجوكاك بسبب انقطاع الطريق الوحيد المؤدي إليها، 

نود أن نحيطكم علما أنه وصلت هذا الصباح أعداد كبيرة جدا من الشاحنات والسيارات وأيضا مساعدات دولية كبيرة، لهذا سنقتصر في الموجة الثانية والأخيرة على بلدتين صغيرتين قرب شيشاوة و امنتانوت لا زالت لم تصلهما إلى الآن المساعدات،

column19:
*Updating the #Sanad_campaign according to the latest developments on the ground*

After the first campaign, which was crowned with success, important and qualitative assistance was provided to 15 isolated roundabouts in the Agokak community due to the blockage of the only road leading to it.

We would like to inform you that very large numbers of trucks and cars arrived this morning, as well as significant international aid. Therefore, in the second and final wave, we will limit ourselves to two small towns near Chichaoua and Amantanot that have not yet received aid.

column9:
We went yesterday the 12th of September to provide some food and other necessities to the victims of the earthquake and while leaving we took a few victim's phone numbers, later on we were contacted by them they explained via WhatsApp that all the help received was detained by the so called " responsible" of the Douar, they stayed all night without shelters because they were not allowed to use the tents and due to the high humidity each morning their clothes are soaked with water, some of them are getting sick and there are a lot of elderly people in the affected area, we are displeased by this matter, people don't have direct access to what we provided them with.
Please do help them once you receive this
Thank you
column10: Douar Essour tidrara- aghouatine- Tahanaout-El Haouz
column11: Please note that any assistance should be directly given to the victims and not to other parties who claim that they will divide it equally, those people steal any type of assistance given and use the victims neediness and weakness to gain more money/power.

column9: Nous intervenons au travers de l’association Adassil pour le développement. L’objectif est de faire des dons de nature suffisamment diverse, de proposer des soins médicaux par 2 médecins, de proposer une écoute psychologique, animer des ateliers par les psychologues et une orthophoniste pour les enfants en leur offrant le matériel utilisé par la suite (papiers, crayons de couleur, jouets…) et surtout rendre leur vie plus joyeuse et vivante en les intégrant, dans la mesure du possible, dans les actions de la caravane.
column11: Une durée de moins de 48h est prévue pour l’action.
column16: Intervention planned in the future / Planned future intervention
column17: Medical Assistance / Medical Assistance, Food and Water / Food and Water, Psychological listening and workshops with speech therapist
column19: We intervene through the Adassil association for development. The objective is to make donations of a sufficiently diverse nature, to offer medical care by 2 doctors, to offer psychological listening, to lead workshops by psychologists and a speech therapist for the children by offering them the equipment used subsequently ( paper, colored pencils, toys, etc.) and above all make their lives more joyful and lively by integrating them, as far as possible, into the actions of the caravan.
column21: A duration of less than 48 hours is planned for the action.

column11:
دوار تزكي هو عبارة عن تكثل لدواوير (من بينها تكنت، إغرم...) تفوق الساكنة 2000 شخص.
الطريق مفتوحة لكن يجب عن يكون السائق معتاد على الطرق الجبلية لأنه هناك منعرجات صعبة.
آخر 7 كيلومترات لا يمكن استعمال السيارات.
يجب استعمال البعير لحمل المساعدات.
طريق صعبة يجب الحذر ولو مشيا
أهم شيء يجب أن يكون التأطير جيدا والاتفاق على كل التفاصيل.
التنسيق القبلي من ممثلي الدوار ( ناس أهل لذلك تبارك الله شاهدنا ذلك بأعيننا)
لا يتم توزيع المساعدات مباشرة لأنه ستكون فوضى ولا يكون التوزيع متوازنا ( هناك مستودع حيث يتم تجميع المساعدات و تقسيمها حسب النوع و بعد ذلك توزيعها بالعدل).
الخيام يجب الحرص على توزيعها و تثبيتها شخصيا باستشارة ممثلي الدوار.

 الشيء الضروري كذلك هو الصرامة والحزم مع ساكني الدوار والدواوير الأخرى وكذلك مع ممثلي الدوار، لأنه سيساعدكم في ظبط الأمور كما اتفق عليه.

والسلام عليكم

column21:
Douar Tazki is a collection of districts (including Teknet, Eghram...) with a population of more than 2,000 people.
The road is open, but the driver must be accustomed to mountain roads because there are difficult turns.
The last 7 kilometers, cars cannot be used.
Camels must be used to carry aid.
It is a difficult road, so be careful even if you are walking
The most important thing is to have good framing and agree on every detail.
Tribal coordination from representatives of the roundabout (people qualified for this, God bless, we saw that with our own eyes)
Aid is not distributed directly because it would be chaos and the distribution would not be balanced (there is a warehouse where aid is collected and divided according to type and then distributed fairly).
Tents must be carefully distributed and installed personally by consulting representatives of the roundabout.

 What is also necessary is strictness and firmness with the residents of the roundabout and other roundabouts, as well as with the representatives of the roundabout, because it will help you in controlling matters as agreed upon.

Peace be upon you
